  "prompt": "What exactly is 'pins and needles?",
  "response": "\"Pins and needles\" is a common term used to describe a tingling, prickling, or numbing sensation that many people experience, often in their hands, arms, legs, or feet. This sensation occurs when pressure is applied to a nerve, disrupting its normal function. When you relieve the pressure, normal sensation returns, often accompanied by the \"pins and needles\" feeling as the nerve returns to its usual state.\n\nThis tingling sensation is usually temporary and harmless, commonly resulting from staying in one position for too long, such as sitting cross-legged or resting on an arm. In rare cases, if it happens frequently or is accompanied by pain or muscle weakness, it could be indicative of an underlying medical condition and might warrant further investigation by a healthcare professional.",
